what is your reaction of the story the jungle book i want the answer not later than tomorrow please i loved it as a child my mother read it to me and i hold very fond memories it was a whole world created the wolves' society bagheera the aloof and beautiful panther wise baloo the bear i hated the disney version with baloo as witless kaa as a villain etc plus i loved the rhythm of kipling's writing now these are the laws of the jungle and many and mighty are they he used language so well made the places feel real and alive except for mowgli there aren't many people in the stories which i liked too the animals are strong and distinct characters subtly drawn of course there were other stories but mowgli and rikkitikitavi were my favorites Mowgli The Jungle Book The Jungle Book (1967 film) Kaa Bagheera Shere Khan Kaa's Hunting Mowgli's Brothers TaleSpin Letting In the Jungle King Louie The Second Jungle Book Feral children in mythology and fiction Rudyard Kipling Tiger! Tiger! (Rudyard Kipling) Jungle Cubs One Life to Live Akela Fantasmic! Peter Pan Feral child Novel Bill Peet Beauty and the Beast (1991 film) Brother Bear AFI 100 Years series Gene Wolfe Chuck Jones Three Little Pigs The Chronicles of Narnia Manga Messua Yu-Gi-Oh! The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy PEZ Stewie Griffin Alignment (role-playing games) Book of Isaiah Nadia: The Secret of Blue Water The Lion King Tiger The Secret of NIMH Winnie-the-Pooh Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Sonic the Hedgehog Scrooge McDuck Kingdom Hearts Transformers: Cybertron Descendants of Darkness Larry Hama The Tick Cutey Honey Another World (TV series) Gray Wolf Donald Duck Who Framed Roger Rabbit Tony Jay Power Rangers: Wild Force The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy (film) Guiding Light Shaggy dog story Animation in the United States in the television era Shrek 2 Conan the Barbarian Fire Emblem: Blazing Sword Minor characters in Sonic the Hedgehog Rave Master Kimba the White Lion 2Step Digimon Darth Vader 